3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed model for simulating Turing machines and for assembly of shapes, which is a topic in computational complexity. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper presents a new model for computation using self-assembly, which is a topic in artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper deals with the assembly of geometric shapes using tiles, which is a topic in computational geometry.
